tafsir[13]{c,v,t}:
  56,19,"It is not like the wine of the world; it’s drinkers will not get headaches nor suffer intoxication."
  56,21,"They will also roam around with the meat of birds their hearts desire."
  56,23,"Like pearls protected within their shells."
  56,24,"As a reward for the good actions they used to do in the world."
  56,31,"And flowing water which never stops."
  56,32,"And many fruits that cannot be counted."
  56,38,"I created them for the People of the Right: those who will be taken towards the right as a sign of their excellence."
  56,39,"They are a group from the nations of the previous Prophets."
  56,42,"They will be among severely hot winds and extremely hot water."
  56,43,"And in the shadow of black smoke."
  56,46,"They used to persist on disbelief in Allah and the worship of idols instead of Him."
  56,48,"“Will our ancient forefathers who died before us also be resurrected?”"
  56,50,"“...will soon be inevitably gathered on the Day of Judgement to be taken to account and requited.”"